body:
I was a bit hesitant to do that as we may face some confusion with existing python functions that use the `batch` word in the name. For example we already have a batch_multiclass_non_max_suppression function defined here https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/master/research/object_detection/core/post_processing.py#L233
In my local models repository I have added a new function which calls the newly defined op. 
Do you have an alternate suggestion for name other than BatchNonMaxSuppression?
